1. What is a Website?
Definition

A website is a collection of web pages that can be accessed through the Internet using a web browser.

Examples
Google
Amazon
Facebook
Components of a Website
Content (Text, Images, Videos)
Structure (HTML)
Design (CSS)
Functionality (JavaScript)


2. What is the Internet?
Definition

The Internet is a global network of interconnected computers that communicate with each other.

Simple Analogy
Computers = Houses
IP Address = House Address
Internet = Road Network
Purpose

Allows devices around the world to exchange information.

3. What is the World Wide Web (WWW)?
Definition

The World Wide Web is a collection of web pages and resources available over the Internet.

Internet vs Web
Internet	Web
Infrastructure	Service running on Internet
Network of devices	Collection of websites
Physical + Logical Network	Information system
Example

The Internet is like roads.

The Web is like shops and buildings connected through those roads.

4. Client-Server Architecture
Client

Device requesting information.

Examples:

Browser
Mobile App
Server

Computer that stores and provides information.

Working
Client sends request
Server receives request
Server processes request
Server sends response
Browser → Request → Server
Browser ← Response ← Server
5. What is a Browser?
Definition

A browser is software used to access and display web pages.

Examples
Google Chrome
Mozilla Firefox
Microsoft Edge
Responsibilities
Send requests
Receive responses
Render HTML
Apply CSS
Execute JavaScript
6. What Happens When You Open a Website?
Example
www.google.com
Steps
User enters URL
Browser asks DNS for IP address
DNS returns IP
Browser sends HTTP request
Server processes request
Server sends HTML/CSS/JS files
Browser renders page
7. URL (Uniform Resource Locator)
Definition

Address used to locate a resource on the web.

Example
https://www.example.com/products
Parts
https://www.example.com/products
│
├── Protocol (https)
├── Domain Name (www.example.com)
└── Path (/products)
8. Domain Name and IP Address
Domain Name

Human-readable address.

Example:

google.com
IP Address

Machine-readable address.

Example:

142.250.183.14
Why Domain Names?

Humans remember names easier than numbers.

9. DNS (Domain Name System)
Definition

DNS translates domain names into IP addresses.

Example
google.com
      ↓
DNS
      ↓
142.250.xxx.xxx
Analogy

DNS = Phone Contact List

You remember a name, not the phone number.

10. HTTP and HTTPS
HTTP

HyperText Transfer Protocol

Used for communication between browser and server.

HTTPS

Secure version of HTTP.

Difference
HTTP	HTTPS
Not encrypted	Encrypted
Less secure	More secure
Port 80	Port 443
11. Frontend vs Backend
Frontend

What users see and interact with.

Technologies:

HTML
CSS
JavaScript
Backend

Handles logic and data.

Technologies:

Python
Java
PHP
Node.js
Diagram
Frontend
   ↓
