12. What is HTML?
HTML = HyperText Markup Language

Purpose:

Creates structure of a web page.

Example:

<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>Hello Students</p>
Analogy

HTML = Skeleton of a Human Body

13. What is CSS?
CSS = Cascading Style Sheets

Purpose:

Controls appearance of web pages.

Example:

h1{
    color:red;
}
Analogy

CSS = Clothes and Appearance

14. What is JavaScript?
Purpose

Adds interactivity to web pages.

Examples:

Button Click
Form Validation
Animations
Dynamic Content
Analogy

JavaScript = Muscles and Brain

